'''Catalin''' refers to a type of plastic that was prevalent in the 1920's.Among it's many uses was material for the encasement of consumer radios. Many radios of this era are classed according to their plastic housing material. Catalin radios are sometimes confused with [[Bakelite (radio)|Bakelite]], another radio case material of that era.



